info.description:
# Introduction
This is a GraphQL / RESt Hybrid micro service for user authentication and user data retrieval.

# Overview
This micro service is built to be consumed by any client; iOS, Android and Web. Built using Apollo Server.

The service utilizes data models. It is important to understand the user schema 

# User Schema
```
{
    first_name:      {
        type: String,
        required: true,
        trim: true,
        index: true,
    },
    last_name:      {
        type: String,
        required: true,
        trim: true,
        index: true,
    },
    alias:      {
        type: String,
        required: true,
        trim: true,
        index: true,
    },
    location:      {
        type: String,
        required: false,
        trim: true,
        index: true,
        default: null
    },
    phone_country_code:	    {
        type: String, 
        lowercase:true, 
        trim: true, 
        index: true,
        sparse: true,//sparse is because now we have two possible unique keys that are optional
        validate:[
            validate({
                validator: 'isNumeric',
                arguments: [7, 20],
                message: 'Not a valid phone number.',
            })
        ]
    },
    phone:	    {
        type: String, 
        trim: true, 
        sparse: true,//sparse is because now we have two possible unique keys that are optional
        validate:[
            validate({
                validator: 'isNumeric',
                arguments: [7, 20],
                message: 'Not a valid phone number.',
            })
        ]
    },
    phone_verified: {
        type: Boolean,
        default: false,
        index: true
    },
    profile_photo_url: {
        type: String,
        default: null
    },
    full_phone_number: {
        type: String,
        index: true,
        trim: true,
        unique: true,
        validate: [
            validate({
                validator: 'isNumeric',
                arguments: [7, 20],
                message: 'Not a valid phone number.'
            })
        ]
    },

    interests: [
       slug: {
        type: String,
        unique: true,
        required: true
       }
    ],
    followers: [ userRef ],
    subscriptions: [ subscription ],

    date: {
        type: Date,
        default: Date.now()
    }
}
```

# Authentication
To authenticate as a user. Follow these steps:

## Register A New User
GraphQL. Sends a verification code to the new user's phone number via SMS.

### Login if user exists
GraphQL. Sends a verification code to the user's phone number via SMS.

## Verify Identity with SMS
GraphQL. Verify a phone number and retrieve a JSON Web Token.

## View User Data
GraphQL. Retrieve data about a user. This method requires Authentication. 

### How to Set Authentication Header
Postman. Use the **Authorization** HTTP Header with value `Bearer {{JWT}}`.

## [PUT] Update User Info
REST. Easily update user information. This method requires Authentication.

graphql.query:
mutation {
    login(
        phone: "5303242463",
        phone_country_code: "1"
    ) {
        success
    }
}

mutation {
    verifyPhoneNumber(
        phone_country_code: "1",
        phone: "5303242463",
        code: "860758"
    ) {
        jwt,
        refreshToken,
        jwt_expiration,
        refresh_expiration,
        author {
            id,
            alias,
            first_name,
            last_name,
            phone_country_code,
            phone,
            full_phone_number,
            location,
            phone_verified,
            profile_photo_url,
            interests {
                id,
                slug  
            },
            subscriptions {
                id,
                type,
                payload
            },
            followers {
                id,
                display_name,
                user_id
            },
            date,
            anonymous,
            last_active, 
            profile_complete
        }
    }
}

mutation {
    sendEmailLoginCode(
        email: "devontrae@gmail.com"
    ) {
        success
    }
}

mutation {
    verifyEmailLoginCode(
        email: "devontrae@gmail.com",
        code: "259368"
    ) {
        jwt,
        refreshToken,
        jwt_expiration,
        refresh_expiration
    }
}

